#### C/Java Code Example: Ethical Consideration in Product Development
```java
public class ProductDevelopment {
    private String productName;
    private boolean ethicalReview;

    public ProductDevelopment(String productName) {
        this.productName = productName;
        performEthicalReview();
    }

    private void performEthicalReview() {
        // Logic to check for potential side effects and ethical implications before release
        System.out.println("Performing ethical review for " + productName);
        ethicalReview = true;  // Assume initial approval unless proven otherwise
    }

    public boolean isSafeForMarket() {
        return ethicalReview;
    }
}
```
:p How does this code ensure the ethical consideration of a product before release?
??x
This code ensures that an ethical review is performed on the product before it can be released to the market. The `performEthicalReview` method checks for potential side effects and ethical implications, setting the `ethicalReview` flag to true if the review passes. The `isSafeForMarket` method returns whether the product has passed this ethical review.
x??

