#### Battery

Battery involves harmful or offensive physical contact intentionally performed by the defendant on the plaintiff, which results in harm and is unexcused. The contact can be harmful (like a punch) or merely offensive (like an unwelcome kiss).

If the act that created the apprehension is completed and results in harm to the plaintiff, it constitutes battery.
:p What distinguishes assault from battery according to the provided text?
??x
Assault involves creating a reasonable apprehension of imminent harm without actual contact. Battery involves harmful or offensive physical contact intentionally performed on the plaintiff, which results in harm.

Example:
```java
public class LegalCase {
    public void analyzeBattery(String defendantAction, String plaintiffsReaction) {
        if (defendantAction.contains("firing gun") && plaintiffsReaction.contains("injured")) {
            System.out.println("It is a battery.");
        } else {
            System.out.println("No battery as no harm was caused.");
        }
    }
}
```
