#### False Imprisonment

False imprisonment involves the intentional confinement or restraint of another person’s activities without justification. It interferes with the freedom to move without restraint, and can be accomplished through physical barriers, physical restraint, or threats of physical force.

Moral pressure does not constitute false imprisonment if the restrained person wishes to be restrained.
:p Define "false imprisonment" according to the provided text?
??x
False imprisonment is when a defendant intentionally confines or restrains another person’s activities without justification. This restriction interferes with the freedom to move without restraint and can involve physical barriers, physical restraint, or threats of physical force.

