In this case, Joan's act of signing the lease and moving out suggests she intended to be bound. Therefore, Kenwood can enforce the lease unless Joan explicitly disaffirms it within a reasonable time after reaching the age of majority or taking other actions that indicate her intent not to be bound by the contract.

