#### Respondeat Superior Doctrine
Respondeat superior is a legal doctrine that holds an employer liable for the torts committed by its employees within the scope of their employment. This doctrine applies when an employee, while performing tasks assigned or authorized by the employer, commits a wrongful act causing harm to another party.
:p Under what doctrine discussed in this chapter might Buy-Mart be held liable for the tort committed by Watts?
??x
Buy-Mart could potentially be held liable under the respondeat superior doctrine. This means that if Watts's actions were within the scope of her employment and she was acting on behalf of Buy-Mart, Buy-Mart would be responsible for any torts she committed.
