#### Revocation of Wills by Physical Acts
A testator can revoke a will through physical acts like burning, tearing, or canceling it. This must be done intentionally and with clear intent to revoke.
:p Can a testator partially revoke a will by physically crossing out parts of it?
??x
Yes, a testator can partially revoke a will by physically crossing out some provisions. However, the crossed-out portions are dropped, and only the remaining portions remain valid. It is not permissible to write new provisions in place of the crossed-out ones without reexecuting the entire will.
```java
public class WillRevocation {
    public void crossOutProvisions(String willText) {
        // Code for crossing out parts of a will text
