#### Legal Considerations in Revoking Wills
When a state statute prescribes specific methods to revoke a will by physical act, only those methods are allowed. Revocation must follow strict formalities and cannot be accidental.
:p What happens if a testator crosses out part of their will without re-executing it?
??x
Crossing out parts of the will does not fully revoke it; instead, the crossed-out portions become invalid, and the remaining text remains valid. However, to make significant changes or add new provisions, the entire will must be reexecuted (signed again) and reattested.
```java
public class WillModification {
    public void modifyWill(String originalWill, String modifiedProvisions) throws Exception {
        // Code for modifying a will without proper re-execution
        if (!modifiedProvisions.isEmpty()) {
            throw new Exception("Modifying the will requires full re-execution.");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Original will remains valid.");
        }
    }
}
```
