#### Specific Bequests in Wills
Background context explaining the concept of specific bequests, which are items or properties explicitly named and transferred to a beneficiary. Discussing what happens when the item is sold before death.
:p Will Roberta inherit her father's 1966 Ferrari under his will if he sells it before his death?
??x
Yes, Roberta would still inherit the specific bequest of her father’s 1966 red Ferrari under his will. Specific bequests are clear instructions to transfer a particular item to a beneficiary regardless of what happens to that item later.

Even though her father sold the 1966 Ferrari and purchased a newer one, this does not affect the validity or enforceability of the specific bequest in the original will. The will specifies "the 1966 red Ferrari," so the current ownership of the car is irrelevant; Roberta would receive the property that matches her father’s description at the time he made the will.

If the will had instead left a sum of money to Roberta for the purchase of such a car, it could have been different. However, specific bequests are irrevocable once made.
